libmtcmaster (0.0.2-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * Precision timing: clock_nanosleep(TIMER_ABSTIME) + precise per-rate frame
    periods (frameFreqNanos), incl. correct 29.97 drop-frame (33366667 ns).
  * Periodic full-frame resync for network transport (default 50 frames/2s);
    new C API MTCSender_setFullFrameResyncInterval. Resync uses a no-settle
    send so it does not disrupt quarter-frame cadence.
  * New additive C API: MTCSender_getTime, MTCSender_setFrameRate,
    MTCSender_getFrameRate (existing 7 symbols unchanged — ABI compatible).
  * Fix log loss when /run/log is not writable by the engine user: fall back
    to stderr (journald). Make SCHED_RR scheduling failure visible (warning).
    (ClickUp 869djtyzp)
  * Fix Makefile libmtcmaster.so.0 symlink target (was a broken .so.0.10 link).
  * Ported from origin/jitter_improvement; preserves connect-by-name (869djtm9j).

 -- Ion Reguera <ion@stagelab.coop>  Thu, 11 Jun 2026 10:55:36 +0200

